data.title: Zing Definition & Meaning
data.meta_description: Zing definition: A brief high-pitched humming or buzzing sound, such as that made by a swiftly passing object or a taut vibrating string.
data.text:
Try adding lemon juice to add an extra zing to salads.

Getting a cup of ginger and lemon tea to put some zing into my morning I get started.

Where many management books are drier than a diver 's underpants this has a freshness and zing about it.

Literary Awards has a certain zing to it.
